{
  "abstract" : [
    {
      "identifier" : "https:\/\/github.com\/swiftlang\/swift-evolution\/blob\/main\/proposals\/0503-suppressed-associated-types.md",
      "isActive" : true,
      "type" : "reference"
    },
    {
      "text" : "",
      "type" : "text"
    },
    {
      "text" : " ",
      "type" : "text"
    },
    {
      "text" : "officially introduced the ability to define protocols with associated types that are ",
      "type" : "text"
    },
    {
      "code" : "~Copyable",
      "type" : "codeVoice"
    },
    {
      "text" : " and\/or",
      "type" : "text"
    },
    {
      "text" : " ",
      "type" : "text"
    },
    {
      "code" : "~Escapable",
      "type" : "codeVoice"
    },
    {
      "text" : " (i.e., “suppressed”), which relaxes the requirement on types conforming to that protocol.",
      "type" : "text"
    },
    {
      "text" : " ",
      "type" : "text"
    },
    {
      "text" : "During the evolution process, a prototype version of this feature existed under the experimental feature",
      "type" : "text"
    },
    {
      "text" : " ",
      "type" : "text"
    },
    {
      "text" : "named ",
      "type" : "text"
    },
    {
      "code" : "SuppressedAssociatedTypes",
      "type" : "codeVoice"
    },
    {
      "text" : ". ",
      "type" : "text"
    },
    {
      "inlineContent" : [
        {
          "text" : "That experimental feature is now deprecated",
          "type" : "text"
        }
      ],
      "type" : "strong"
    },
    {
      "text" : " and is source-incompatible with the accepted",
      "type" : "text"
    },
    {
      "text" : " ",
      "type" : "text"
    },
    {
      "text" : "version detailed in SE-503.",
      "type" : "text"
    }
  ],
  "hierarchy" : {
    "paths" : [
      [
        "doc:\/\/diagnostics\/documentation\/diagnostics",
        "doc:\/\/diagnostics\/documentation\/diagnostics\/diagnostic-groups"
      ]
    ]
  },
  "identifier" : {
    "interfaceLanguage" : "swift",
    "url" : "doc:\/\/diagnostics\/documentation\/diagnostics\/old-suppressed-associatedtypes"
  },
  "kind" : "article",
  "metadata" : {
    "role" : "article",
    "roleHeading" : "Article",
    "title" : "Migrating away from experimental suppressed associated types (OldSuppressedAssociatedTypes)"
  },
  "primaryContentSections" : [
    {
      "content" : [
        {
          "anchor" : "overview",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Overview",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "This document provides high-level guidance for users of this experimental feature to help them",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "update their code to be compatible with ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "https:\/\/github.com\/swiftlang\/swift-evolution\/blob\/main\/proposals\/0503-suppressed-associated-types.md",
              "isActive" : true,
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : ".",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "Please see the evolution proposal for complete details of the accepted functionality.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Source-Changes",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Source Changes",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "content" : [
            {
              "inlineContent" : [
                {
                  "text" : "The difference between the prototype experimental feature and SE-503 is with its treatment of primary associated types that are suppressed.",
                  "type" : "text"
                }
              ],
              "type" : "paragraph"
            },
            {
              "inlineContent" : [
                {
                  "text" : "Thus, if your suppressions were only on associated types that are ",
                  "type" : "text"
                },
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "not",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "strong"
                },
                {
                  "text" : " primary i.e., not mentioned within the angle",
                  "type" : "text"
                },
                {
                  "text" : " ",
                  "type" : "text"
                },
                {
                  "text" : "brackets of the protocol in which they’re defined, then there are no source changes required.",
                  "type" : "text"
                }
              ],
              "type" : "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name" : "Note",
          "style" : "note",
          "type" : "aside"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Primary associated types are those that are mentioned within angle brackets of a protocol:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "protocol Mailbox<Items> {",
            "  \/\/            ^~~~~~~ declares that `Items` is a primary associated type",
            "  ",
            "  associatedtype Items: ~Copyable",
            "  associatedtype Generator: ~Copyable",
            "  ",
            "  \/\/ ...",
            "}"
          ],
          "syntax" : "swift",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Relative to the prototype, ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "https:\/\/github.com\/swiftlang\/swift-evolution\/blob\/main\/proposals\/0503-suppressed-associated-types.md",
              "isActive" : true,
              "overridingTitle" : "SE-503",
              "overridingTitleInlineContent" : [
                {
                  "text" : "SE-503",
                  "type" : "text"
                }
              ],
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : "",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "infers default requirements for primary associated types in places they were not already. The defaults are expanded",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "within extensions of the protocol:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "extension Mailbox {} \/\/ OLD",
            "extension Mailbox where Items: ~Copyable {} \/\/ NEW"
          ],
          "syntax" : "swift",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "The defaults are also expanded in generic contexts where a conformance requirement involving that protocol is written.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "So, to preserve existing behavior, you’ll need add explicit suppressions on the associated types induced by those",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "conformance requirements within those contexts:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "func foo<T>(..) where T: Mailbox {} \/\/ OLD",
            "func foo<T>(..) where T: Mailbox, T.Items: ~Copyable {} \/\/ NEW",
            "",
            "struct PostOffice<M: Mailbox> {} \/\/ OLD",
            "struct PostOffice<M: Mailbox> where M.Items: ~Copyable {} \/\/ NEW"
          ],
          "syntax" : "swift",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "ABI-Changes",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "ABI Changes",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "content" : [
            {
              "inlineContent" : [
                {
                  "text" : "This section is only of interest to who distribute pre-built shared libraries and declared a public",
                  "type" : "text"
                },
                {
                  "text" : " ",
                  "type" : "text"
                },
                {
                  "text" : "protocol that has a suppressed primary associated type.",
                  "type" : "text"
                }
              ],
              "type" : "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name" : "Note",
          "style" : "note",
          "type" : "aside"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "The implementation of SE-503 changes the mangling scheme for generic signatures as a result of the inferred defaults.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "Suppose you have this protocol:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "protocol Drink<Flavor> {",
            "  associatedtype Flavor: ~Copyable",
            "}"
          ],
          "syntax" : "swift",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "and these two functions that are completely explicit about whether ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "T.Flavor",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " is Copyable or not:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "func foo<T: Drink>(_ t: T) where T.Flavor: Copyable {}",
            "func bar<T: Drink>(_ t: T) where T.Flavor: ~Copyable {}"
          ],
          "syntax" : "swift",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "In the prototype version of the feature, ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "bar",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : "’s requirement ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "T.Flavor: ~Copyable",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " was redundant, whereas",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "foo",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : "’s requirement ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "T.Flavor: Copyable",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " was ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "inlineContent" : [
                {
                  "text" : "not",
                  "type" : "text"
                }
              ],
              "type" : "emphasis"
            },
            {
              "text" : " redundant, so it would be included in the mangled symbol of ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "foo",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ":",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "$s1X3fooyyxAA5DrinkRzs8Copyable6FlavorRpzlF ---> X.foo<A where A: X.Drink, A.Flavor: Swift.Copyable>(A) -> ()",
            "$s1X3baryyxAA5DrinkRzlF ---> X.bar<A where A: X.Drink>(A) -> ()"
          ],
          "syntax" : null,
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "With SE-503, this ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "inlineContent" : [
                {
                  "text" : "almost",
                  "type" : "text"
                }
              ],
              "type" : "emphasis"
            },
            {
              "text" : " flips around. It’s now ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "foo",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " whose requirement is redundant, and ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "bar",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : "’s mangled symbol now",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "mentions the requirement ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "T.Flavor: ~Copyable",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ":",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "$s1X3fooyyxAA5DrinkRzlF ---> X.foo<A where A: X.Drink>(A) -> ()",
            "$s1X3baryyxAA5DrinkRz6FlavorRj_zlF ---> X.bar<A where A: X.Drink, A.Flavor: ~Swift.Copyable>(A) -> ()"
          ],
          "syntax" : null,
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "It’s possible to preserve the old symbol for ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "bar",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " by using ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "@abi",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " to produce its symbol as if ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "T.Flavor: Copyable",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ":",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "\/\/ $s1X3baryyxAA5DrinkRzlF ---> X.bar<A where A: X.Drink>(A) -> ()",
            "@abi(func bar<T: Drink>(_ t: T) where T.Flavor: Copyable)",
            "func bar<T: Drink>(_ t: T) where T.Flavor: ~Copyable {}"
          ],
          "syntax" : "swift",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "But, only ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "https:\/\/github.com\/swiftlang\/swift\/blob\/main\/docs\/StandardLibraryProgrammersManual.md#_silgen_name",
              "isActive" : true,
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : " can be used preserve ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "foo",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : "’s old mangled symbol ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "$s1X3fooyyxAA5DrinkRzs8Copyable6FlavorRpzlF",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ".",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind" : "content"
    }
  ],
